This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it focuses on improving resource utilization in warehouse-scale data centers. Additionally, the use of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) engines suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The consideration of dynamic pricing models and user request information suggests a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect. Finally, the use of a hierarchical and hybrid approach may also suggest a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
